<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="526" pageId="7" pageNumber="524" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1599,2028]" pageId="7" pageNumber="524">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1599,1626]" pageId="7" pageNumber="524">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Metope with very weak (traces) median and sublateral carinae. Forewing radius and media running parallel or diverging from the basal cell at acute angle. Hind tibia with two lateral spines. Lateral margins of male anal tube without processes (in lateral view). Lobe-shaped processes of phallobase basement narrowing apically. Aedeagus with strongly curved ventral hooks, thicker in their middle parts. Style with deeply concave hind margin; capitulum on long neck. Forewings with dark brown dots sometimes fused in dark brown to black wide median band; apical cells with large dark brown spots. Total length: males—3.7–4.0 mm, females—4.0–4.9 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1599,2028]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1436,150,249]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="525" pageId="7" pageNumber="524">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,534,1815,1841]" pageId="7" pageNumber="524">Supplementary description.</emphasis>
Metope wide (usually weakly visible from above), enlarged below eyes, with very weak median and sublateral carinae; upper margin weakly concave (
<figureCitation box="[1001,1089,1851,1877]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–11" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1757,1781]" captionTargetBox="[170,1420,788,1682]" captionTargetId="figure-298@6.[151,1436,776,1701]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 9–11. Lethierium cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), male, Timhadit. 9—dorsal view; 10—lateral view; 11—frontal view. Scale bar—1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691457" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691457/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="524">Figs 11</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1104,1136,1851,1877]" captionStart="FIGURES 39–40" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[205,1382,209,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-15@13.[195,1393,199,1876]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 39–40. Lethierium cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), male, Timhadit. 39—face; 40—head and pronotum, dorsal view. Out of scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691489" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691489/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="524">39</figureCitation>
). Coryphe transverse, 3–4 times as wide as long at midline, margins keel-shaped; anterior margin weakly convex; posterior margin deeply concave (
<figureCitation box="[217,290,1923,1949]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–11" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1757,1781]" captionTargetBox="[170,1420,788,1682]" captionTargetId="figure-298@6.[151,1436,776,1701]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 9–11. Lethierium cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), male, Timhadit. 9—dorsal view; 10—lateral view; 11—frontal view. Scale bar—1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691457" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691457/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="524">Figs 9</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[302,334,1923,1949]" captionStart="FIGURES 39–40" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[205,1382,209,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-15@13.[195,1393,199,1876]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 39–40. Lethierium cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), male, Timhadit. 39—face; 40—head and pronotum, dorsal view. Out of scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691489" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691489/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="524">40</figureCitation>
). Pronotum 1.3–1.5 times as long as coryphe medially, without carinae, but with a median groove. Mesonotum 1.3 times as long as pronotum, with weak lateral carinae. Forewings with distinct knee prominences and relief veins, with many transverse veins in its apical halves. Forewing vein sequence (
<figureCitation box="[1106,1189,1995,2021]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–11" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1757,1781]" captionTargetBox="[170,1420,788,1682]" captionTargetId="figure-298@6.[151,1436,776,1701]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 9–11. Lethierium cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), male, Timhadit. 9—dorsal view; 10—lateral view; 11—frontal view. Scale bar—1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691457" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691457/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="524">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
): R 3 (R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1283,1291,2014,2028]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="524">1</subScript>
not reaching wing margin), firstly furcating at basal third of wing; M 4–5, firstly furcating at wing middle, M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1209,1217,169,183]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="525">1</subScript>
and M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1294,1302,169,183]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="525">2</subScript>
furcating in apical third of wing; CuA1. Radius and media running parallel or diverging from the basal cell at acute angle. Hind tibiae with two lateral spines and 7–10 apical spines. First metatarsomere with 6–7 intermediate spines.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691465" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6691465" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691465/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="525" startId="8.[151,264,1521,1545]" targetBox="[151,1433,273,1498]" targetPageId="8">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1521,1582]" pageId="8" pageNumber="525">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,340,1521,1546]" pageId="8" pageNumber="525">FIGURES 16–19.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Gnezdilov, 2022" authorityName="Gnezdilov" authorityYear="2022" box="[345,567,1522,1546]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Lethierium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinatum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[345,567,1522,1546]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="525">Lethierium carinatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[573,653,1522,1546]" pageId="8" pageNumber="525">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[573,653,1522,1546]" pageId="8" pageNumber="525" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, female paratype, Bou Naceur. 16—dorsal view; 17—lateral view; 18—frontal view; 19—caudal view. Scale bar—1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1628,1942]" pageId="8" pageNumber="525">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1628,1654]" pageId="8" pageNumber="525">Coloration.</emphasis>
General coloration yellowish light brown. Metope light brown, with yellowish median carina and with two pairs of elongate yellowish spots—medially besides of the carina and above clypeus; traces of larval sensory pits dark brown to black. Metopoclypeal suture black. Coryphe dark brown, with light brown yellowish median line. Rostrum dark brown to black. Scapus black. Pedicel dark brown. Pro- and mesonotum light brown yellowish, with black traces of larval sensory pits. Forewings light brown, with dark brown dots and spots sometimes fused in dark brown to black wide median band. Apical cells of forewings with large dark brown to black spots. Membrane veins light yellow. Legs brown yellowish to dark brown. Apices of leg spines and of 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1106,1120,1844,1858]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="525">rd</superScript>
metatarsomeres dark brown to black. Abdominal tergites black. Abdominal sternites light brown to dark brown, except female sternite III dark brown medially. Gonoplacs dark brown to black, each with light yellow lateral spot.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691469" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6691469" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691469/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="526" startId="9.[151,264,1302,1326]" targetBox="[156,1425,159,1271]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1302,1362]" pageId="9" pageNumber="526">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,344,1302,1326]" pageId="9" pageNumber="526">FIGURES 20–22.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Lethierry, 1878)" baseAuthorityName="Lethierry" baseAuthorityYear="1878" box="[354,732,1302,1326]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Lethierium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reiberi">
<emphasis box="[354,543,1302,1326]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="526">Lethierium reiberi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lethierry, M. L." box="[560,724,1302,1326]" pageId="9" pageNumber="526" pagination="25 - 31" refId="ref9505" refString="Lethierry, M. L. (1878) Homopteres nouveaux d'Europe et des contrees voisines. Pt. 2. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de Belgique, 21, 25 - 31." type="journal article" year="1878">Lethierry, 1878</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, male, Aïn Sefra. 20—face; 21—head and pronotum, dorsal view; 22—hind wing. Out of scale.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1408,2011]" pageId="9" pageNumber="526">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,529,1408,1435]" pageId="9" pageNumber="526">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[384,516,1408,1434]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–46" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1513,1537]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,188,1454]" captionTargetId="figure-28@14.[151,1436,181,1462]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 41–46. Lethierium cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), Timhadit, male genitalia. 41—anal tube and pygofer, lateral view; 42—anal tube, dorsal view; 43—style, lateral view; 44—style, dorsal view; 45—penis, ventral view; 46—penis and connective, lateral view. Out of scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691491/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="526">Figs 41–46</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Anal tube enlarged medially, twice as long as wide medially, apex widely rounded (in dorsal view) (
<figureCitation box="[342,424,1444,1471]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–46" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1513,1537]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,188,1454]" captionTargetId="figure-28@14.[151,1436,181,1462]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 41–46. Lethierium cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), Timhadit, male genitalia. 41—anal tube and pygofer, lateral view; 42—anal tube, dorsal view; 43—style, lateral view; 44—style, dorsal view; 45—penis, ventral view; 46—penis and connective, lateral view. Out of scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691491/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="526">Fig. 42</figureCitation>
), lateral margins without processes (in lateral view) (
<figureCitation box="[1010,1093,1444,1471]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–46" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1513,1537]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,188,1454]" captionTargetId="figure-28@14.[151,1436,181,1462]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 41–46. Lethierium cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), Timhadit, male genitalia. 41—anal tube and pygofer, lateral view; 42—anal tube, dorsal view; 43—style, lateral view; 44—style, dorsal view; 45—penis, ventral view; 46—penis and connective, lateral view. Out of scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691491/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="526">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
). Anal column short, ¹⁄ of anal tube. Lobe-shaped processes of phallobase basement wide, narrowing apically (
<figureCitation box="[1023,1105,1480,1507]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–46" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1513,1537]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,188,1454]" captionTargetId="figure-28@14.[151,1436,181,1462]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 41–46. Lethierium cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), Timhadit, male genitalia. 41—anal tube and pygofer, lateral view; 42—anal tube, dorsal view; 43—style, lateral view; 44—style, dorsal view; 45—penis, ventral view; 46—penis and connective, lateral view. Out of scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691491/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="526">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
). Ventral phallobase lobe with a small apical notch (
<figureCitation box="[388,470,1516,1543]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–46" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1513,1537]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,188,1454]" captionTargetId="figure-28@14.[151,1436,181,1462]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 41–46. Lethierium cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), Timhadit, male genitalia. 41—anal tube and pygofer, lateral view; 42—anal tube, dorsal view; 43—style, lateral view; 44—style, dorsal view; 45—penis, ventral view; 46—penis and connective, lateral view. Out of scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691491/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="526">Fig. 45</figureCitation>
). Apical aedeagal processes long and wide, narrowing apically. Aedeagus with strongly curved ventral hooks, thicker in its middle parts, arising below its middle. Style with deeply concave hind margin; caudo-dorsal angle widely rounded (
<figureCitation box="[513,595,1588,1615]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–46" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1513,1537]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,188,1454]" captionTargetId="figure-28@14.[151,1436,181,1462]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 41–46. Lethierium cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), Timhadit, male genitalia. 41—anal tube and pygofer, lateral view; 42—anal tube, dorsal view; 43—style, lateral view; 44—style, dorsal view; 45—penis, ventral view; 46—penis and connective, lateral view. Out of scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691491/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="526">Fig. 43</figureCitation>
); capitulum on long neck, not narrowing apically (in dorsal view) (
<figureCitation box="[1327,1409,1588,1615]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–46" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1513,1537]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,188,1454]" captionTargetId="figure-28@14.[151,1436,181,1462]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 41–46. Lethierium cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), Timhadit, male genitalia. 41—anal tube and pygofer, lateral view; 42—anal tube, dorsal view; 43—style, lateral view; 44—style, dorsal view; 45—penis, ventral view; 46—penis and connective, lateral view. Out of scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691491/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="526">Fig. 44</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1408,2011]" pageId="9" pageNumber="526">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,634,1624,1651]" pageId="9" pageNumber="526">
Female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[409,537,1624,1650]" captionStart="FIGURES 64–70" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1215,1239]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,187,1184]" captionTargetId="figure-28@18.[151,1436,181,1192]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 64–70. Lethierium spp., female. 64—L. cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), Ras el ma, sternite VII, dorsal view; 65—same, ventral view; 66—L. reiberi (Lethierry, 1878), Mékalis, sternite VII, dorsal view; 67—L. juniperi (Bergevin, 1915), Aïn Kerma, sternite VII, dorsal view; 68—same, ventral view; 69—L. carinatum sp. nov., paratype, Bou Naceur, anal tube, dorsal view; 70—L. carinatum sp. nov., paratype, Bou Naceur, sternite VII, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691513" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691513/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="526">Figs 64, 65</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[549,621,1624,1650]" captionStart="FIGURES 71–77" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1708,1732]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,189,1675]" captionTargetId="figure-15@19.[151,1436,181,1685]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 71–77. Lethierium spp., ovipositor structure, 71–75—L. juniperi (Bergevin, 1915), Aïn Kerma, 76–77—L. cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), Ras el ma. 71—anal tube and gonoplac, dorsal view; 72, 76—gonapophyses IX and gonospiculum bridge, lateral view; 73—same, ventral view; 74—gonapophysis VIII; 75—apex of endogonocoxal lobe; 77—basement of gonapophyses IX and gonospiculum bridge, caudal view. Out of scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691517" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691517/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="526">76, 77</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Hind margin of sternite VII with large semicircular labial process medially (
<figureCitation box="[210,296,1660,1687]" captionStart="FIGURES 64–70" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1215,1239]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,187,1184]" captionTargetId="figure-28@18.[151,1436,181,1192]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 64–70. Lethierium spp., female. 64—L. cedricolum (Dlabola, 1989), Ras el ma, sternite VII, dorsal view; 65—same, ventral view; 66—L. reiberi (Lethierry, 1878), Mékalis, sternite VII, dorsal view; 67—L. juniperi (Bergevin, 1915), Aïn Kerma, sternite VII, dorsal view; 68—same, ventral view; 69—L. carinatum sp. nov., paratype, Bou Naceur, anal tube, dorsal view; 70—L. carinatum sp. nov., paratype, Bou Naceur, sternite VII, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6691513" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6691513/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="526">Fig. 64</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor structure generally as in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bergevin" baseAuthorityYear="1915" box="[726,847,1661,1686]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Lethierium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="juniperi">
<emphasis box="[726,847,1661,1686]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="526">L. juniperi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Anal tube convex (in lateral view), long, 3.5 times as long as wide medially, narrowing apically, with rounded apex (in dorsal view). Anterior connective lamina of gonapophysis VIII with three teeth in lateral group.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
